{
  "extends": "./node_modules/gts/tsconfig-google.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    // base configuration at root level
    "esModuleInterop": true,
    "skipLibCheck": true,
    "target": "es2022",
    "module": "es2022",
    "moduleResolution": "node",
    "allowJs": true,
    "checkJs": true,
    "resolveJsonModule": true,
    "moduleDetection": "force",
    "isolatedModules": true,
    "strict": true,
    "noUncheckedIndexedAccess": true,
    "noImplicitOverride": true,
    // disable eslint checks
    "lib": ["dom", "es2022"], // Removes: Cannot find name 'window'.
    "noImplicitAny": false, // Removes: Parameter implicitly has an 'any' type.
    "strictNullChecks": false, // Removes: Cannot invoke an object which is possibly 'undefined'.
    // package configuration at root level
    "declaration": true,
    "composite": true,
    "sourceMap": true,
    "declarationMap": true,
  },
  "files": [],
  "references": [
    { "path": "./packages/util-event/tsconfig-package.json" },
    { "path": "./packages/util-route/tsconfig-package.json" },
    { "path": "./packages/util-server/tsconfig-package.json" },
    { "path": "./packages/util-type/tsconfig-package.json" },
  ],
  // 1. "include" property applies eslint rules to listed directories and files.
  // 2. Breaks "pnpm compile" and displays errors in PROBLEMS panel but fixes errors with eslint typescript parser that literally say 'Parsing error: "parserOptions.project" has been provided for @typescript-eslint/parser. The file was not found in any of the provided project(s): <file>'.
  // 3. Parsing errors disappear except for **/eslint.config.js. Fixed in eslint.config.mjs.
  // 4. Found additional parameters to disable eslint checks but couldn't remove 'Cannot write file because it would overwrite input file' errors in tsconfig.json.
  // 5. Workaround to fix 4 is to enable "include" property before linting and disable "include" after linting. Reference: https://bencane.com/understanding-exit-codes-in-bash-6942a8b96ce5. Note that single quotes were changed to double quotes to resolve passing 'lint;' instead of 'lint' to "pnpm gts".
  // "include": ["src", "packages"],
}
